titleStmt.title: O England; thy time is come, God hath not taken thee until thou be ful; yea, the fulness of thy time is come ...
titleStmt.author: Simmonds, Martha.

notesStmt.note: Title taken from first lines of text.
Attributed by Wing and Smith to Martha Simmonds; Smith gives "[Part by James Nayler, Hannah Stranger, and W.T.]".
Reproduction of the original in the Haverford College Library, Pennsylvania.
